Additionally, shaded coffee agroforests play an important role as mitigation action. Carbon stocking and sequestration have been documented in the biomass associated with the shade tree component of coffee agroforestry, making the system a carbon sink (
 Coltri et al., 2015; 
 Segura et al., 2006; 
 Gay et al., 2006). Shaded-grown coffee is important to preserve natural resources (
 Perfecto and Vandermeer, 1996; 
 Jha et al., 2014), improving biodiversity, social and financial characteristics (
 Lin, 2007).
